<topic xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" base="Princeton" id="Get_Features_Arbitration" xml:lang="en-US">
  <title>Arbitration (feature identifier 0x01)</title>

  <body>
    <p>The firmware's arbitration is hardwired to
    round-robin.</p>

    <fig id="Arbitration_Command_Control_Flow_2pht97qqbq">
      <title>Arbitration Command Control Flow</title>

      <image href="Graphics/Admin Command Manager/Set_Feature_Arbitration.svg" placement="break" width="5.5in"/>
    </fig>

    <table id="_2qht97qqbq">
      <title>Arbitration Command Control Flow</title>

      <tgroup cols="3">
        <colspec colname="c1" colwidth="4*"/>

        <colspec colname="c2" colwidth="17*"/>

        <colspec colname="c3" colwidth="79*"/>

        <thead>
          <row>
            <entry>No.</entry>

            <entry>Message</entry>

            <entry>Description</entry>
          </row>
        </thead>

        <tbody>
          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">1</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CmdReady64</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The command is
            received by one of the Data Managers.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">2</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CmdReady</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Data
            Manager forwards the command to the Admin Command Manager for
            processing.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">3</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CplQueueUpdate</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Admin
            Command Manager sends a completion queue update request to the
            Completion Manager.</p></entry>
          </row>

          <row>
            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">4</b> </p></entry>

            <entry><p> <b otherprops="bold">CplQueueUpdateCpl</b>
            </p></entry>

            <entry><p>The Completion
            Manager replies back to the Admin Command Manager when the
            completion has been successfully sent to the host.</p></entry>
          </row>
        </tbody>
      </tgroup>
    </table>

    <draft-comment translate="no">This command
    returns invalid opcode because hardware round robin is
    used.</draft-comment>

    <draft-comment translate="no">This command
    should return unsupported feature when NVMe spec is
    updated.</draft-comment>
  </body>
